genresAdvancedInfo.name: cape verdean folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rooted in the traditional music of the Cape Verdean islands, Cape Verdean folk is a genre that celebrates the rich cultural heritage of this small nation off the coast of West Africa. With influences from Portuguese, African, and Brazilian music, Cape Verdean folk is characterized by its soulful melodies, intricate rhythms, and poetic lyrics.
